a really hard time with it.

00:40:09.940 --> 00:40:13.090
And you don't often
hear about this.

00:40:13.090 --> 00:40:16.620
And so when that happened
to me, I was very surprised.

00:40:16.620 --> 00:40:19.580
And I was like,
what did I do wrong?

00:40:19.580 --> 00:40:22.807
Why am I having a hard time?

00:40:22.807 --> 00:40:24.640
And I'm wondering, have
you ever experienced

00:40:24.640 --> 00:40:25.660
something like that?

00:40:25.660 --> 00:40:27.490
NIRALI SHAH: Oh,
yeah, I can deeply

00:40:27.490 --> 00:40:29.980
resonate with some of
what you are saying.

00:40:29.980 --> 00:40:32.630
I don't know which
retreat you went to.

00:40:32.630 --> 00:40:37.780
But I can definitely
tell you that it is

00:40:37.780 --> 00:40:40.840
a very, very skillful process.

00:40:40.840 --> 00:40:42.910
It's a very skillful practice.

00:40:42.910 --> 00:40:46.210
And over time, I
have seen that there

00:40:46.210 --> 00:40:50.080
are times when I have driven
myself a bit too hard.

00:40:50.080 --> 00:40:55.180
And it has taken me some time
to recover and heal that.

00:40:55.180 --> 00:40:58.660
So absolutely.

00:40:58.660 --> 00:41:03.250
I think it really helps to have
a very skilled teacher, a very

00:41:03.250 --> 00:41:07.540
experienced teacher, who you
can check in with very deeply

00:41:07.540 --> 00:41:12.880
and who can understand you
very quickly also because there

00:41:12.880 --> 00:41:17.410
isn't sometimes a lot of times
at these retreats to talk.

00:41:17.410 --> 00:41:22.060
But for me, it's also been--
if I could share one thing--

00:41:22.060 --> 00:41:26.530
that as I meditated,
I started experiencing

00:41:26.530 --> 00:41:31.340
some very beautiful
states of great beauty,

00:41:31.340 --> 00:41:36.790
I mean, great expansion, a
great sense of connectedness,

00:41:36.790 --> 00:41:43.780
of feeling really connected
to something much vaster.

00:41:43.780 --> 00:41:45.710
And a lot of times,
I would actually not

00:41:45.710 --> 00:41:50.380
tell my teachers of this because
sometimes, some teachers, they

00:41:50.380 --> 00:41:54.070
are not skilled, and
they don't have--

00:41:54.070 --> 00:41:56.080
I mean, they can
reflect it back at you

00:41:56.080 --> 00:42:01.640
in a way which might not
support you at that time.

00:42:01.640 --> 00:42:05.990
So it's very
important to go slow.

00:42:05.990 --> 00:42:08.740
And the last thing
also I can tell you

00:42:08.740 --> 00:42:13.080
is that working with emotions
is not an easy practice.

00:42:13.080 --> 00:42:14.530
And any time you
meditate, you are

00:42:14.530 --> 00:42:16.750
going to face strong emotions.

00:42:16.750 --> 00:42:21.130
And it's very important to
learn how you work with emotions

00:42:21.130 --> 00:42:25.690
because if you go too much,
it can destabilize you.

00:42:25.690 --> 00:42:28.960
And so there's a whole
somatic piece around this.

00:42:28.960 --> 00:42:31.480
And you don't want to get
overwhelmed, because if you do,

00:42:31.480 --> 00:42:33.460
your nervous system
will go into a flight,

00:42:33.460 --> 00:42:35.410
fight, or freeze response.

00:42:35.410 --> 00:42:37.540
And that can be hard.

00:42:37.540 --> 00:42:40.840
So for me, a lot
of my practices,

00:42:40.840 --> 00:42:43.900
like really practicing delight.

00:42:43.900 --> 00:42:46.000
It's not all suffering
and hard work.

00:42:46.000 --> 00:42:47.860
A lot of this
meditation practice

00:42:47.860 --> 00:42:52.960
is learning to take in
great, great delight.

00:42:52.960 --> 00:43:00.520
So much of the way we function,
when very difficult or painful

00:43:00.520 --> 00:43:03.970
experiences come in, our
system is not ready to take it,

00:43:03.970 --> 00:43:05.710
and we put it under the carpet.

00:43:05.710 --> 00:43:10.720
And at the same time, when very,
very pleasurable experiences

00:43:10.720 --> 00:43:12.850
come, we do the same thing.

00:43:12.850 --> 00:43:16.780
We put great pleasure
under the carpet,

00:43:16.780 --> 00:43:20.440
because the mind, the
ego, wants to stay

00:43:20.440 --> 00:43:23.980
in this lukewarm,
neutral territory.

00:43:23.980 --> 00:43:31.270
And it doesn't have the
capacity to take in.

00:43:31.270 --> 00:43:36.130
And so over time, you start
building a greater capacity

00:43:36.130 --> 00:43:38.870
to work with these emotions.

00:43:38.870 --> 00:43:39.710
I don't know.

00:43:39.710 --> 00:43:42.050
Does that answer your question?

00:43:42.050 --> 00:43:43.705
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

00:43:43.705 --> 00:43:51.800
When you do overdo it, how
do you balance it back?

00:43:51.800 --> 00:43:56.520
What's the best way
to balance yourself?

00:43:56.520 --> 00:43:59.020
NIRALI SHAH: So I can
give you an example.

00:43:59.020 --> 00:44:00.490
I was at a retreat.

00:44:00.490 --> 00:44:04.330
And some deep
stuff, trauma stuff

00:44:04.330 --> 00:44:08.470
came up for me from 15
years ago or something,

00:44:08.470 --> 00:44:09.580
like really old stuff.

00:44:09.580 --> 00:44:14.030
And it was hard.

00:44:14.030 --> 00:44:17.050
And what I did is I
stopped meditating.

00:44:17.050 --> 00:44:17.860
I got up.

00:44:17.860 --> 00:44:19.520
I went to my room.

00:44:19.520 --> 00:44:20.920
I took a nice shower.

00:44:20.920 --> 00:44:23.320
I wore some nice clothes.

00:44:23.320 --> 00:44:25.100
I went for a beautiful walk.

00:44:25.100 --> 00:44:27.220
I hung out with the deer.

00:44:27.220 --> 00:44:29.020
I looked at the flowers.

00:44:29.020 --> 00:44:34.270
I enjoyed a nice cup of tea,
really, really relaxing myself.

00:44:34.270 --> 00:44:37.540
And then after a few hours,
I went back on the cushion.

00:44:37.540 --> 00:44:41.170
And I had a lot more
capacity to be with that.

00:44:41.170 --> 00:44:43.390
And then again, I
would see, OK, this

00:44:43.390 --> 00:44:45.020
is getting too intense for me.

00:44:45.020 --> 00:44:47.260
So now I'm going to take
in some more delight

00:44:47.260 --> 00:44:52.630
because I don't want to
stretch my nervous system.

00:44:52.630 --> 00:44:55.000
AUDIENCE: My question
is around meditation

00:44:55.000 --> 00:44:59.440
as a personal practice
